parameters:
\n<Grandpa>Therefore, the Catfield family has always taken it upon
themselves to elevate and maintain the status of our
beastkin, to be equal to humans, and to continue being good
friends...
1ルイ真顔
\n<Rui-Chan>...
1ワンズ普通3
\n<Wadsworth>...
\n<Grandpa>Young master!! Young lady!!

\n<Grandpa>Were you listening to my story? Do you understand what I am
doing right now?
1ルイ真顔2

\n<Rui-Chan>Yes, Grandpa. You are explaining the mindset that we, as
beastkin who will carry on the honorable Catfield family's
future, should have.

\n<Grandpa>No, I am scolding the naughty kittens who broke my precious
vase.

\n<Grandpa>At least, how about looking down here and showing some
remorse?
1ワンズぶりっこ

\n<Wadsworth>I'm sorry, Grandpa. Please forgive me♥ My tail accidentally
hit it♥

\n<Grandpa>Sigh... It seems there have been some problems with your
behavior lately.

\n<Grandpa>How many windows, plates, and pots have you broken this
month? How many wallpapers have you scratched, how many
pillars have you snapped, and do you know how much the
repair costs have been?
1ワンズぶりっこ

\n<Wadsworth>I was just practicing with Rui-Sham. I didn't mean to break
them. Grandpa, it wasn't on purpose♥ Do you understand?
1ルイ普通2

\n<Rui-Chan>It was an accident during training, a result of the act of
self-improvement. In other words, it's a consequence of
having the awareness of being the heir to this house.

\n<Grandpa>Sigh... Young master, young lady. Are you that concerned
about Miss Chelsea?
1ワンズ怒り

\n<Wadsworth>Father called sister a "failure." She couldn't do magic, a
"disgrace to the family." That's why he kicked her out of
the house, right?

\n<Grandpa>Miss Chelsea left this house of her own accord. She had her
own reasons for doing so.
1ワンズ怒り2

\n<Wadsworth>I know! She was pushed to leave! Father only thinks about
protecting the house. He doesn't think of us as anything
more than heirs!

\n<Grandpa>That's not true...! Please don't speak ill of the head of
the family. He is thinking about you and the future of the
beastkin...
1ワンズ困惑

\n<Wadsworth>Sister wasn't very smart, and she was a bit of a
troublemaker...
1ワンズ泣き

\n<Wadsworth>But you know, she was kinder than anyone else. Being kind is
much harder than magic or studying.

\n<Grandpa>It's been several months since Miss Chelsea left. I am
worried as well. Of course, the head of the family is also
distressed.

\n<Grandpa>However, as twins with innate talent, you young master and
young lady are special.

\n<Grandpa>I understand that it's hard to focus on your studies and
training. But if this continues, we won't be able to face
your late mother...
1ルイ照れ2
\n<Rui-Chan>...Let's go already. Wadsworth.
\n<Grandpa>Sigh... My... vase...
\n<Grandpa>Miss Chelsea... where are you now...
